<paragraph blockId="3.[192,1441,1047,1492]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1860" box="[232,350,1047,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[232,350,1047,1071]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Trichoxys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chevrolat, L. A." box="[567,770,1048,1072]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="451 - 504" refId="ref11462" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. 1860. Description d'especes de Clytus propres au Mexique. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (3) 8: 451 - 504." type="journal article" year="1860">Chevrolat (1860)</bibRefCitation>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Laicharting, 1784" authorityName="Laicharting" authorityYear="1784" box="[980,1285,1047,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Clytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[980,1059,1047,1071]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Clytus</emphasis>
Laicharting, 1784
</taxonomicName>
. He included 14 species in the group but did not designate a 
<typeStatus box="[766,819,1081,1105]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
species. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Thomson, J." box="[1009,1205,1080,1104]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref12693" refString="Thomson, J. 1861. Tribu. Cerambycitae. p. 129 - 396. In: J. Thomson. Essai d'une classification de la famille des cerambycides et materiaux pour servir a une monographie de cette famille. Chez l'auteur et au Bureau du Tresorier de la Societe entomologique de France; Paris. 396 p." type="book" year="1861">Thomson (1861)</bibRefCitation>
elevated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1860" box="[1322,1440,1080,1104]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1322,1440,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Trichoxys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to genus level and designated 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat, 1860" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1860" box="[563,1117,1112,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Clytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilineatus" subGenus="Trichoxys">
<emphasis box="[563,642,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Clytus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[658,776,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Trichoxys</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[793,915,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">bilineatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chevrolat, L. A." box="[922,1117,1112,1137]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="451 - 504" refId="ref11462" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. 1860. Description d'especes de Clytus propres au Mexique. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (3) 8: 451 - 504." type="journal article" year="1860">Chevrolat, 1860</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus box="[1160,1213,1113,1137]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1860" box="[1322,1440,1112,1136]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1322,1440,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Trichoxys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently composed of 15 species, all of them recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[936,1022,1145,1169]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Mexico</collectingCountry>
with five of the species extending their known distribution into Central America (
<bibRefCitation author="Tavakilian, G. &amp; H. Chevillotte" box="[758,1146,1177,1201]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref12647" refString="Tavakilian, G., and H. Chevillotte. 2018. Titan, base de donnees internationales sur les Cerambycidae ou longicornes. Version 3.0. Available at http: // titan. gbif. fr /. (Last accessed 2018 December.)" type="url" year="2018">Tavakilian and Chevillotte 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezark, L. G." box="[1156,1310,1177,1201]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref11231" refString="Bezark, L. G. 2019. A Photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the New World. Available at https: // apps 2. cdfa. ca. gov / publicApps / plant / bycidDB / wsearch. asp? w = n (Last accessed January 2019.)" type="url" year="2019">Bezark 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lingafelter, S. W. &amp; J. E. Wappes" box="[192,574,1210,1234]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="154 - 162" refId="ref11848" refString="Lingafelter, S. W., and J. E. Wappes. 2012. A new species of Trichoxys Chevrolat (Cerambycidae: Cerambycinae: Clytini) from Mexico, with a key to known species. The Pan-Pacific Entomologist 88 (2): 154 - 162." type="journal article" year="2012">Lingafelter and Wappes (2012)</bibRefCitation>
provided a diagnosis for the genus as follows: “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1860" box="[1163,1411,1209,1234]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1163,1281,1209,1233]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Trichoxys</emphasis>
Chevrolat
</taxonomicName>
is characterized from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1839" box="[496,581,1242,1266]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Clytini">Clytini</taxonomicName>
by 1) the abruptly recessed parasutural region of the elytron that starts at the anterior one-third and diverges more widely to the apex where it is approximately one-third of the discal width, and the strongly elevated anterior portion of the mesosternum (appearing abruptly recessed from ventral view) and 2) the evenly rounded pronotum that is distinctly narrower than the elytral base and without calli or lateral asymmetry. All the known species have bold, pubescent patterns on the elytra which are easily diagnostic for each species.” They also placed 
<taxonomicName authority="Linsley, 1935" authorityName="Linsley" authorityYear="1935" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochraetheoides">
<emphasis box="[1134,1440,1403,1427]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Trichoxys ochraetheoides</emphasis>
Linsley, 
<quantity box="[298,357,1436,1460]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.914899999999999" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="1935.0">1935</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chevrolat, 1860)" baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[592,953,1436,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtellus">
<emphasis box="[592,729,1436,1460]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">T. hirtellus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chevrolat, L. A." box="[745,944,1436,1460]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="451 - 504" refId="ref11462" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. 1860. Description d'especes de Clytus propres au Mexique. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (3) 8: 451 - 504." type="journal article" year="1860">Chevrolat, 1860</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lingafelter &amp; Wappes" authorityYear="2012" box="[1089,1223,1436,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichoxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penrosei">
<emphasis box="[1089,1223,1436,1460]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">T. penrosei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new species, and provided a key to the species based on their illustrations of elytral patterns.
</paragraph>
